{
  "page": "Sword of the Morning",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg/250px-Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"626\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f3/Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg/375px-Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f3/Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg/500px-Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jose_Daniel_Cabrera_PenaSwordOfTheMorning.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A Sword of the Morning carrying Dawn, as depicted by José Daniel Cabrera Peña in <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i></div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Sword of the Morning</b> is a title of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Dayne\" title=\"House Dayne\">House Dayne</a> bestowed on the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> who bears the ancestral <a href=\"/index.php/Greatsword\" title=\"Greatsword\">greatsword</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Dawn\" title=\"Dawn\">Dawn</a>. Only a knight of House Dayne who is deemed worthy can carry it.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> For this reason, the <i>Swords of the Morning</i> are all famous throughout the Seven Kingdoms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\nIf there is no Dayne knight considered worthy, the title lies dormant. The last to bear the title was Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>, a famed knight of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Former_Swords_of_the_Morning\">Former Swords of the Morning</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sword_of_the_Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Former Swords of the Morning\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Dayne\" title=\"Davos Dayne\">Davos Dayne</a>, husband of Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Nymeria\" title=\"Nymeria\">Nymeria</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_ten_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_ten_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Ulrick_Dayne\" title=\"Ulrick Dayne\">Ulrick Dayne</a>, who was considered one of the greatest knights of his time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Arthur_Dayne\" title=\"Arthur Dayne\">Arthur Dayne</a>, the last Dayne to bear the title <i>Sword of the Morning</i>. A <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> of great renown.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok21.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sword_of_the_Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: See also\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Sword_of_the_Morning_(constellation)\" title=\"Sword of the Morning (constellation)\">Sword of the Morning (constellation)</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Sword_of_the_Morning&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/So_Spake_Martin\" title=\"So Spake Martin\">So Spake Martin</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.westeros.org/Citadel/SSM/Entry/1395/\">US Signing Tour (Albuquerque, NM) (November 29, 2005)</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafdorne:_the_andals_arrive.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Dorne: The Andals Arrive.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_ten_thousand_ships.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B